article.headline: SMU 70, Colorado 67
article.story: DALLAS -- Bamba Fall scored 13 points and had 11 rebounds to help lead SMU to a 70-67 win over Colorado on Monday night. Derek Williams led the Mustangs (5-7) with 14 points. Colorado cut SMU's lead to two at 69-67 with five seconds left. Cory Higgins fouled Fall, who made one of his two free throws. Nate Tomlinson missed a 3-pointer as time ran out that would have tied the game. Paul McCoy scored 11 for SMU and Mouhammad Faye had 10. Dwight Thorne II led Colorado (7-6) with 18 points. Austin Dufault had 13, Higgins 11 and Jermy Jackson-Wilson and Tomlinson each scored 10. Colorado led 33-32 at the half but SMU used a 9-3 run to start the second half to take the lead for good.
